The paper deals with the problem of interference mitigation and power control in cellular networks, which is a central topic in the field of networked systems and communication. The use of carrier aggregation and game theory to design a distributed algorithm for power control suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) or cs.IT (Information Theory). The focus on network performance and optimization also suggests that the paper could be classified under cs.SY (Systems and Control) or cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the use of game theory to design the algorithm suggests that the paper could also be classified under cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory).
